<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Hostages-Glance     05-05 0434</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Hostages-Glance,0451</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hostages in Lebanon At-A-Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-France-Hostages, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of nine Americans and nine other people kidnapped
in Lebanon and still missing:
   _ Terry A. Anderson, 40, chief Middle East correspondent for The
Associated Press, kidnapped March 16, 1985. He was born in Lorain,
Ohio, and raised in Batavia, N.Y.
   _ Thomas Sutherland, 57, acting dean of agriculture at the
American University of Beirut, abducted June 9, 1985. A
Scottish-born American, Sutherland was on leave from the faculty of
Colorado State University.
   _ Frank Herbert Reed, 55, the American director of the Lebanese
International School, kidnapped Sept. 9, 1986. He is from Malden,
Mass.
   _ Joseph James Cicippio, 57, of Norristown, Pa., acting
comptroller at the American University in Beirut, kidnapped Sept.
12, 1986.
   _ Edward Austin Tracy, 57, a writer and native of Rutland, Vt.
   _ Robert Polhill, 53, of New York City, a lecturer in accounting
at Beirut University College, kidnapped Jan. 24, 1987.
   _ Alann Steen, 49, a communications instructor at Beirut
University College, kidnapped Jan. 24, 1987. Steen is a Boston
native.
   _ Jesse Jonathan Turner, 40, a visiting professor of mathematics
and computer science at Beirut University College, kidnapped Jan.
24, 1987. He is native of Boise, Idaho.
   _ U.S. Marine Lt. Col. William R. Higgins, 43, head of an
observer group attached to the U.N. peacekeeping force in Lebanon,
kidnapped Feb. 17, 1988. He was born in Danville, Ky.
   _ Mithileshwar Singh, 60, Indian. A visiting professor of
finance at Beirut University College since 1982, Singh was
kidnapped Jan. 24, 1987.
   _ Terry Waite, 48, a British envoy of the Anglican Church who
was seeking the release of foreign hostages, disappeared Jan. 20,
1987. He reportedly is being held by pro-Iranian kidnappers though
no group has claimed responsibility for his abduction.
   _ John McCarthy, 30, British television journalist, kidnapped
April 17, 1986.
   _ Alec Collett, 66, a British journalist on assignment with the
United Nations Relief and Works Agency, kidnapped March 25, 1985. A
terrorist group said in April 1986 that he was hanged and released
a videotape purportedly showing Collett hanging from a scaffold,
but his body was never found.
   _ Italian businessman Alberto Molinari, kidnapped Sept. 11, 1985.
   _ Brian Keenan, 35, an Irish teacher of English at the American
University of Beirut, kidnapped April 11, 1986.
   _ West German businessman Rudolf Cordes, 53, kidnapped Jan. 17,
1987, after arriving in west Beirut. He is Beirut manager of the
West German chemical concern Hoechst AG.
   _ Two people of unknown nationality were kidnapped on Jan. 26,
1987.
</TEXT>
