<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     05-05 0382</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0393</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quiet Morning Across The Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain and a few thunderstorms drenched the mid-Atlantic states
today during a generally calm morning across the nation.
   However, strong and gusty winds were expected to move into the
Southwest today. Advisories have been posted for winds later today
and tonight across Southern California and the flaming gorge
portion of Utah.
   Also, a high wind watch for today was posted over the western
valleys of Utah.
   Early morning rainshowers and a few thunderstorms reached from
eastern Ohio, Pennsylvania and southern New Jersey across the
Virginias, the Carolinas and eastern Georgia.
   Rainshowers also were scattered across western Montana and
snowshowers were widely spread in the mountains of north-central
California.
   The forecast for today called for showers and thunderstorms over
the mid-Atlantic states and the central Appalachians; rain across
the Pacific Northwest into the northern Rockies; and generally
sunny skies over the rest of the nation with cloudy skies
prevailing over parts of the central California valleys.
   Highs were expected in the 50s along the northern and central
Pacific coast, the upper Ohio Valley and the central Appalachians;
the 80s through much of Texas, the Oklahoma panhandle and the Gulf
of Mexico coast into central and southern Florida; the 90s over
south-central Texas east of the Pecos River; and the 60s or 70s
elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 30
degrees at the air base near Minot, N.D., to 76 degrees at Phoenix,
Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 55 fair; Boston 56 cloudy; Buffalo 54 cloudy;
Charleston, S.C. 62 cloudy; Cincinnati 50 partly cloudy; Cleveland
49 rain; Detroit 52 partly cloudy; Miami 70 fair; New York 52
cloudy; Philadelphia 53 rain; Pittsburgh 51 foggy; Portland, Maine
43 partly cloudy; Washington 57 foggy.
   _Central: Bismarck 38 fair; Chicago 51 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
54 fair; Denver 51 fair; Des Moines 58 fair; Indianapolis 42 fair;
Kansas City 52 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 51 fair; Nashville 45
fair; New Orleans 65 fair; St. Louis 47 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 57 fair; Anchorage 41 cloudy; Las Vegas 65
cloudy; Los Angeles 55 partly cloudy; Phoenix 73 fair; Salt Lake
City 54 cloudy; San Diego 57 cloudy; San Francisco 49 fair; Seattle
46 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 45 fair; Toronto 41 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
