<HEAD>Worker Gets Baggage Compartment Trip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An airline baggage worker took a 70-minute
jet ride to Seattle _ in the luggage compartment next to a coffin.
   The Boise Air Service employee's problems began Tuesday when he
was loading the coffin into an Alaska Airlines 727 and other
workers accidentally locked him in.
   Surprised Alaska Airlines employees in Seattle found the man
after the plane landed about 4:35 p.m., airline spokesman Lou
Cancelmi said.
   The man was uninjured and returned to Boise on another flight.
This time, he sat in the passenger compartment.
   Alaska Airlines and Boise Air Service refused to identify the
employee, who they said was embarrassed.
