<1ST_LINE>r w PM-TaxFreedom     05-05 0101</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Tax Freedom,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>This is Tax Freedom Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This is ``Tax Freedom Day'' and you are
working for yourself the rest of the year.
   The Tax Foundation, a Washington research organization,
estimates that if everything you earned were earmarked for taxes
until your debt was paid, the average American would have been
working for the government this year through May 4.
   That is the latest date since the foundation began making the
calculation to emphasize the federal, state and local tax burden.
The exercise assumes that all taxes, including those collected by
business, are paid by individuals.
</TEXT>
