<HEAD>Man Stabbed After Catching Burglar Kissing Girlfriend</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VICKSBURG, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was stabbed several times by a
burglar after he woke up to find the intruder trying to kiss his
girlfriend, authorities said.
   Raymond Barrentine, 33, was reported in stable condition at the
Vicksburg Medical Center after undergoing surgery for stab wounds
in his back and chest.
   His girlfriend and the assailant were unhurt in the struggle
early Wednesday.
   Police arrested Anthony Bell, 22, wearing blood-soaked clothing,
at a convenience store. He was being held in lieu of $50,000 bond,
facing charges of burglary and aggravated assault, Chief of
Detectives Bob Woods said.
   Barrentine and his girlfriend were asleep at his house when she
awoke to find a man trying to kiss her and began screaming.
   Woods said the two men fought and Barrentine was stabbed at
least five times with a six-inch hunting knife.
   ``They fought all over that house,'' Vicksburg police
investigator Mark Culbertson said. ``They tore that house up. There
was blood everywhere.''
   Culbertson said there was no indication the burglar knew
Barrentine or the woman. After the fight, the intruder ran outside,
broke windows with a steel object and ran away, Culbertson said.
