<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Astronauts,0138</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviet Cosmonauts Invited To Air Show</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sponsors of the Aerospace America '88 air
show are trying to arrange a reunion of American Apollo astronauts
and Soviet Soyuz cosmonauts who were together on a joint space
mission.
   Stanley Draper Jr. of the Oklahoma City Chamber of Commerce said
cosmonauts Alexei Leonov and Valerie Kubasov have been invited to
attend the June 17-19 air show at Will Rogers World Airport.
   If they can make it, they would be joined by astronauts Thomas
Stafford, Deke Slayton and Vance Brand.
   All five were in orbit in July 1975 on the first cooperative
international space flight, when they joined their spacecraft for
44 hours.
   Draper said Stafford, who is from Oklahoma, has arranged for
sponsors to pay the cosmonauts' way to Oklahoma.
