<HEAD>Two Killed, Five Kidnapped in Crime Spree</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GIRARD, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A burglar kidnapped a family of four today,
then shot to death an elderly couple and held one woman hostage,
authorities said. The hostage escaped and police later arrested a
suspect.
   Police said the crime spree began around 3 a.m. with a burglary
attempt at the home of William Morris, 44, his wife, Dea, 43, and
their sons, Robert and William, both 15.
   The intruder forced the family to drive approximately 50 miles
from their home near Spartansburg to Girard, where all four were
released unharmed.
   Dr. Mary Love, 69, and her husband, Frank, were slain by rifle
shots just before dawn in their home near Girard, said state
Trooper William Shaffer.
   After the Loves were slain, their assailant left in the couple's
car, holding a gun to the head of his hostage, police said.
   The woman, who was not immediately identified, got away
unharmed, said Shaffer, although he did not know how she escaped.
   Shaffer said the suspect was identified as Donald Harry Fultz,
35, of Union City. He was being held by state police but was not
immediately charged with any crime.
