<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Swiss Avalanche,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Victims In Wednesday's Disaster All Swiss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHUR, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said Thursday that a woman and
four men, all from Switzerland, died in an avalanche in the
Engadine Alps.
   The giant snowslide Wednesday swept down Mt. Sissone close to
the Swiss-Italian border, burying the five skiers under more than
seven feet of snow.
   It was the season's second-worst avalanche following an April 1
slide just under Mt. San Lorenzo, also in the Engadine, that killed
six Dutch members of a ski party.
   Wednesday's avalanche raised the death toll in the Swiss
mountains from avalanches to 25 so far this year. There were no
other details on the latest victims.
</TEXT>
