<HEAD>Advisory Panel On Rural Health Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Iowa Gov. Robert D. Ray was named
Thursday to chair a new 18-member committee that will advise the
Department of Health and Human Services on health care services in
rural areas.
   Department Secretary Otis R. Bowen announced the membership of
the new National Advisory Committee on Rural Health and said it was
part of an effort ``to address rural America's significant health
care problems.''
