<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--DuquesnePresident     05-05 0104</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Duquesne President,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Duquesne Appoints Its First Lay President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Duquesne University on Thursday named John E.
Murray as the first lay president in the Catholic school's 110-year
history.
   The 55-year-old University of Pittsburgh law professor succeeds
the Rev. Donald S. Nesti, president since 1980, who resigned in
August.
   Murray earned an undergraduate degree at LaSalle University. He
received law degrees from Catholic University of America and the
University of Wisconsin. He has taught law at the University of
Pittsburgh since 1986.
   Murray will be the first president who is not a priest in the
Holy Ghost order, which founded Duquesne.
</TEXT>
