<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Inches Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
249,292 cars and trucks this week, down from last week's 249,889,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 240,550 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 159,979 cars this
week, compared with 163,031 a week ago and 162,403 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 89,313, compared
with last week's 86,858 and last year's 78,147.
   Canadian automakers were to build 26,882 cars this week,
compared with 26,500 last week and 11,984 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 21,417, compared
with 21,060 last week and 17,727 in the same week last year.
